{
  "query": "Considering different timber harvesting methods, which are most effective for increasing understory plant diversity?",
  "relevant_summary": "Shelterwood harvesting has shown consistent positive effects on understory plant diversity, with six of seven studies finding increased abundance, species richness and diversity of understory plants (Action ID: 1223). Group-selection harvesting produced mixed results, with four of eight studies showing increased cover and diversity of understory plants, while two studies found decreased understory species richness and biomass (Action ID: 1224). Clearcutting also demonstrated variable outcomes, with eight of twelve studies finding increased cover and species richness of understory plants, while two found decreased density and species richness (Action ID: 1222). The removal of woody debris after timber harvest showed limited benefits for understory diversity, with most studies finding no effect or mixed effects on species richness and diversity (Action ID: 1213).",
